cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for detecting great apes in camera trap footage. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves attention-based feature blending, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep learning models for object detection and feature extraction also suggests the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with robotics and automation, as it aims to assist human camera trap inspection efforts, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of video data, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
